The architects looked in - the office also includes a kindergarten
The Avriopoint office building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch.Design.
But who would expect a mini-kindergarten here, with everything that belongs to it: colorful walls, creative furniture, a lot of toys and even a mini-playground on the outdoor terrace.
This kindergarten has been available to Arch.Design employees since last year.
The design and architecture office Arch.Design, from whose studios a number of well-known Brunner buildings come, calculated from the first designs for the new Avriopoint building with the premises for its company mini-garden.
Most of its 90 employees (inside) are in the babyboom age and the company is committed to ensuring that the project aunts and architects return to their workplace as soon as possible.
Together with the opportunity to work shorter, the kindergarten is another bonus that Arch.Design has to offer to its employees in the concept of their social program.
Building engineers and architects find it so much easier to put their demanding profession and childcare under one hat.
The Minikindergarten is an original idea of the employees (inside) of Arch.Design and with the support of the management, they managed to earn funding from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs for their project.
The operating mini-kindergarten is financed through the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment Policy from the European Social Fund and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to this funding (subsidies amounting to CZK 2.8 million) the necessary facilities and equipment could be purchased and for the duration of 2 years is provided for qualified personnel and for the operation.
After the funding has been exhausted (2 years), the company Arch.Design is obliged to continue operating the mini kindergarten for a further 3 years at its own expense.
The preparation of this project took a full year, with the company Economy Rating providing effective assistance in the processing of the application.
The children are taken care of by fully qualified staff - a nurse and a kindergarten teacher, children can visit the kindergarten without age restrictions, although most of them are over three years old.
And since it is a mini kindergarten, only 5 children may be present at the same time, however, the day alternates over several children.
The kindergarten business is flexibly tailored to the needs of the parents, the children of all employees have the same rights in terms of the use of the kindergarten - regardless of the company hierarchy and their respective position.
Although it is about individual education and care, the program content in the mini kindergarten is still comparable to the framework program of pre-school education.
The children not only play here, they are offered excellent lessons - from basic knowledge to pre-school lessons, in addition they also learn English.
The classroom is equipped not only with toys and creative games, but also with a computer that is available to children.
What's more - the presence of young children in the company contributes to a friendly and positive company environment.
Parents can take a look at the children at any time and thus eliminate the stress in the delayed pick-up of the children from a distant kindergarten.
Parents are making more productive use of their working hours.
No wonder natural and loyal employer-employee relationships are also being formed here.
Arch.Design has thus joined the Czech companies, which offer significant benefits when recruiting new employees, which are family-friendly and through such programs strengthen their personal marketing.
A bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Look at the interiors of Gaudi
The roof is like the back of a prehistoric owl, the staircases like the spine of a dinosaur and the balconies are shattered fish mounds.
This is the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> by the Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi in Barcelona.
From the local inhabitants, the house with its organic forms received the nickname "Bone House".
Organic shapes, wild colors, the unusual use of stone, tiles and mosaics, the shale-like facades and ubiquitous soft lines, all these are typical features of Antonio Gaudi’s youthful style.
The facade of the house plays with dreamy lines, tender colors and textures reminiscent of nature and living things.
It is only with closer observation that everything is dominated by geometry, rhythm and thoughtful order.
At night, the entire fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade appears even more plastic, dramatic and the special lighting enhances the brightness of the colors.
The same swinging lines and convex shapes also dominate the interior of the house.
Wave-shaped wood replicates the window frames, railings, decorative elements of doors, even eyelets and bars.
The Batll<0xC3><0xB3> house in the Eixample district on the bustling shopping street Passeig de Gr<0xC3><0xA1>cia No. 43 was built by the architect Emilio Sala Cortese in 1877.
The reconstruction took two years and was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, originally consisted of the demolition of the old and the construction of a completely new building, but eventually he agreed to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s idea of an unusual and also cheaper reconstruction.
The rental house Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, however, was not designed by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> alone.
He worked with the architect Josep Maria Jujol.
It was precisely on its zipper that the decorations for the representative apartment of the real estate owner were created and also the use of mosaics on the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade was his idea.
However, many other painters and artists also contributed to the design of the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
The joint work on the designs for the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> was the beginning of a fruitful collaboration between Jujola and Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Jujol also participated in the construction of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s Casa Mil<0xC3><0xA1> house in the Park Güell, which also houses other works by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Shortly after its completion, the house received its organic forms from the local inhabitants due to the nickname "Bone House".
Others, in turn, called it the special window opening mechanism because of the "walking house".
It is also said that at the top of the building is depicted the sword of Saint George, the patron saint of Catalonia.
But also other pictorial elements symbolize hidden religious motifs.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> designed for the house a unique central heating system with ventilation ducts and typical fireplaces.
A bit bizarre already encourages their 45-degree inclination.
In his work, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> consistently ignored all the construction regulations of the time and did not let any of them be misled.
Before the start of construction, he obtained the corresponding building permit from the city, but the information he provided about the planned reconstruction was so vague that the city fathers were so dissatisfied with the result two years later when it was completed that they asked for remediation.
Among other things, the councillors also encountered the fact that the construction with its pillars even intervened in the public civic ladder.
There were no changes, however, on the contrary - just fifteen days after the district's request in this regard, Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3> submitted an application for approval of the rental of the two highest floors of the house - and it was promptly granted to him.
The owner of the house himself moved into the lower floors.
In the gallery on the 2nd floor there was a meeting room, on the third floor there were the bedrooms and private rooms of the apartment.
The ground floor was leased to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey building runs a staircase up to the roof terrace.
Due to the basic elements of the conversion, all right angles and straight lines were removed and replaced by curved and curved walls.
But Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with a modern concept for the interconnection of spaces.
The social part can be fully connected by opening the salon doors, and so a larger society could comfortably chat without having to give up a certain intimacy in more intimate conversations.
The house received a rather unusual roof and two other floors thanks to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>'s renovation, in addition to a new facade.
Also impressive is Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play with the light as well as the blue and white glazed tiles with which the courtyard is decorated and the lighthouses.
The play of these two colors gives all floors of the house a maximum level of light.
In doing so, he simply used the principle that white reflects light better than dark colors that absorb sunlight on the contrary.
The Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, which was included in the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2005, can be visited by anyone today.
On the first floor, the most spacious and magnificent apartment is made accessible to the public.
The owners of the house decided to take this step only in the year and this on the occasion of the 150th birthday of the famous creator.
When it was discovered that this is a fairly profitable business, the visits were kept, yes, they were also extended to other common areas and the attic spaces, including the roof terrace.
However, the price for visiting the building monument is not a cardboard stick, it is 16.50 euros, students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist cards get a 20% discount.
This amount exceeds the entry prices to other Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> buildings in the city.
If you want to get to know the real atmosphere of the house with its dragon towers, you should try to make friends with one of the house dwellers and visit him at home.
The right mattress and the right bed rest? Women have different desires than men
Not the best bed frame, but the quality of the bed surface - so mattress and rust make the good bed.
However, these need to complement each other harmoniously in order to meet the wishes of the specific user.
Many things play a role in the selection - the weight, the size, the state of health and, last but not least, the sex of the sleeper.
Equally important is the interior, in which mattresses and rust are subordinated.
Typical example?
In a weekend house where it is not heated regularly, latex mattresses are not well suited, as they take much longer to "get warm".
In addition, they are significantly heavier than conventional polyurethane mattresses.
And - they should be turned regularly.
If they do not have enough ventilation ducts in the core and are still lying on a solid plate, moisture is added: so it is not excluded that it forms under their mold.
Of course, the choice also plays a role in what you are used to.
Those who have been abroad for a long time, where very high mattresses with a soft layer are common, will be unable to get used to a low mattress with a hard surface.
“Almost all the ice hockey players who came back from the NHL complained to me that they couldn’t sleep here properly.”
"For their shuffled shoulders, heels and hips, they just need a soft layer of visco foam (Memory Foam - a form memory polymer)."
"I recommend these also to people with diabetes who suffer from a disorder of the nervous system, so that they can receive the "information" from the joints and the skin poorly," explains Sylva Hadamczikov<0xC3><0xA1>, who specializes in upholstery furniture.
That’s why many ice hockey players, but also other customers, have been worried about these mattresses with visco foam (Memory Foam) years ago.
"Today, this is no longer a problem, because such mattresses are offered by the manufacturer Tempur, the Italian company Magniflex or the Czech manufacturer Tropico."
And you don’t necessarily have to be a famous ice hockey player to learn to appreciate the benefits of visco foam.
This “miracle” actually works.
The foam optimizes its hardness and shape according to the absorbed heat, in other words, it fits right on the warm body.
Nowhere does it push, at night you don’t roll around like after a heavy fight.
You just sleep a lot better.
The viscoelastic foam also offers protection against decubitus (wundbrand).
When choosing the mattress size, you should still add the length of the soles to the body size, i.e. about 21 to 34 cm.
A man and a woman who are 180 cm tall need a bed that is 210 to 220 cm long.
Each of the sleepers should have at least 90 cm of bed width, i.e. 180 cm together.
For single beds, for example for singles, 120 to 140 cm are suitable.
Comfort halfway and also for potential visitors.
Otherwise, the following rule of thumb applies to the ideal bed width: "If you lie on your back, there should still be enough room for the slightly angled arms", advises Ing. Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, the master of the upholstery and room exhibitor, who for years has been concentrating on the problem of the problem of the sleeping of the migraine and the earth.
With a double bed, everyone needs their own rust and their own mattress, but be careful when shopping, so that the mattresses are equally high.
Otherwise, there is nothing left but to mount the rust at different heights and this is not possible with every bed frame.
Foam mattresses should be at least 14 cm high, mattresses with spring skeleton 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters should fall on the mold layer and the fine pad.
"With your hand or when setting back you must not feel the springs in any case," warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a special type of rust.
Fully upholstered beds with mattresses and bedding, such as mattresses and mattresses, have nothing to look for in the bedroom.
These mattresses can not be ventilated and the cover can not be washed, which is already going on today.
And since you lose between 0.2 and 0.75 liters of sweat in a single night, it is clear that the mattress slowly becomes a giant (and clogged) sieve after five to seven years.
That’s why professionals reject advertising slogans that promise a lifespan of up to 25 years for mattresses, and even a lifetime warranty.
Every thing has its ifs and buts.
And therefore a practical advice from the dealers: for mattresses of 120 or 140 cm width, you should not shy away from the hygiene of the washable, removable covers, yet it is recommended to use a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Even though mattress covers are usually made with round zippers today, so that you get two halves after opening (immeasurably important for the washing process and the size of the washing machine!), the manipulation with larger mattresses, especially alone, often has to be carried out, like the uneven fight between David and Goli.
Do they have a solid plate in the bed instead of a roast?
Get out of here!
Or at most for a bed for unloved guests and for a single night.
Also, they should rather provide the plate with ventilation holes (if they are not already inside) and use mattresses with a spring skeleton and a minimum height of 15 cm with so-called pocket springs and fine pads.
Polyurethane mattresses do not belong on such a substrate.
Latex or sandwich mattresses are suitable for non-adjustable lattice grilles with 14 to 18 spring strips (latex or sandwich mattresses, if any, also combinations of latex and coconut), always pay off rusts with a greater number of lattices, i.e. 28 or more spring strips, with the possibility of regulating the Lord's support in the lanyard and the lapel area.
Adjustable laminate grilles do not include mattresses with spring skeleton, as they do not respond to the ergonomic adjustment.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the spring strips, special flexible shoulder modules are also available.
This involves a special fastening of the spring strips, which allows the spring strips to be pressed in or even angled in such a way that they allow the shoulders of the sleeper to sink punctually.
Especially for men with wide shoulders an important thing.
There are even manufacturers of mattresses that have begun to use soft zones for the shoulder area in "man's mattresses".
The ladies are also thought of - they are given these soft zones in the hip area.
For the most demanding customers, point-elastic wing spring systems (lattoflex) or rost with point-elastic contact pads with so-called multitorsion suspension are designed.
The pressure is distributed over several points, which reduces the voltage.
But - if you use a bad (too big and full) pillow for the right mattress and the right rust, most of the benefits are lost again.
Here, too, a rule of thumb: the pillow should support the head, its tips should only reach up to the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
Ideally, therefore, a 50 x 60 cm pillow appears, as the Scandinavians like it, for example.
In the lateral position, the head cushion (along with the shoulder relief zone in the rust or the soft zone in the mattress) should balance the shoulder height.
Our modern mattresses have something in common with the old straw bags (filled with hay).
Modern manufacturers are increasingly using natural materials or at least their blends.
Even with mattresses, the new magic word is "bio".
Instead of petroleum raw materials, natural oils are increasingly used to make polyurethane foams - for example, castor oil and soybean oil.
Soy is used by all known manufacturers.
“Bio is the essence of mattresses made from purely natural materials,” explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used in the production of mattress covers - one of the first was Aloe Vera.
However, you can also use microcapsules that spread fresh forest or lavender scent when you sleep.
Here, too, we make a difference between a man and a woman.
While a "cooling" plant extract from birch leaves is used in men so that the mattress cover can absorb heat and cool the body, the covers have a "warming" effect for women.
Extracts from red peppers stimulate blood circulation, so the weaker sex becomes comfortable when sleeping.
What about today's favorites?
