Zapatero seems to have understood that too, and his dual announcement (the promised reforms after the meeting with the big companies last Saturday and the announcement of new measures from yesterday) points out that despite criticizing Merkel, Weg has the hypothesis of creating order in her own home.
But the red line drawn by Germany is there, and it doesn’t look like it would change anything.
